The paper deals with the problem of optimal auction design, which is a classic topic in the field of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The introduction of a model where bidders can be distinguished based on side information also suggests a potential connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Finally, the use of empirical risk minimization techniques is a common tool in the field of computational economics (cs.EC).
